  "description": "The (3,4) spiral torus — an unexplored WEAVE-III family. Three revolutions around the torus hole, four through the core. pqScale = 0.5 + 0.5*sin(0.75*pi) = 0.854: the maximum-asymmetry point along the sin curve is not at (2,5) but at (1,1) — yet (3,4) produces the most complex intermediate value, between trefoil and cinquefoil. Triangle strands for warm harmonic softness. High-pass filter at 2200 Hz removes the sub-fundament and presents only the spectral overtone structure of the knot coupling. The result shimmers.",
